events.name: Alabama Crimson Tide at Auburn Tigers

headlines.description: Jarrett Stidham passed for 237 yards and ran for a fourth-quarter touchdown and No. 6 Auburn beat top-ranked Alabama 26-14 Saturday with a berth in the Southeastern Conference title game on the line.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 6 Auburn tops No. 1 Alabama 26-14, earns SEC title shot

events.name: Clemson Tigers at South Carolina Gamecocks

headlines.description: Kelly Bryant threw two touchdowns to Hunter Renfrow and No. 4 Clemson kept on track for a third straight trip to the College Football Playoff with a 34-10 victory over rival South Carolina on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bryant leads No. 4 Clemson to 34-10 win over Gamecocks

video.headline: Clemson rolls past South Carolina

events.name: West Virginia Mountaineers at Oklahoma Sooners

headlines.description: Baker Mayfield threw for 281 yards and three touchdowns after being punished for directing a lewd gesture toward the Kansas bench last week, and Oklahoma routed West Virginia 59-31 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mayfield leads No. 3 Oklahoma past West Virginia, 59-31

video.headline: Oklahoma tops West Virginia on senior day

events.name: Wisconsin Badgers at Minnesota Golden Gophers

headlines.description: Alex Hornibrook threw three touchdown passes without an interception for fifth-ranked Wisconsin, and the Badgers easily remained unbeaten by overwhelming rival Minnesota 31-0 on Saturday for their 14th straight victory over the Gophers.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hornibrook, Badgers stay unbeaten with 31-0 win at Minnesota

video.headline: Wisconsin blanks Minnesota

events.name: Georgia Bulldogs at Georgia Tech Yellow Jackets

headlines.description: Sony Michel ran for 85 yards and a touchdown, Jake Fromm threw two touchdown passes and No. 7 Georgia protected its playoff hopes with a dominant 38-7 win over Georgia Tech on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 7 Georgia protects playoff hopes, crushes Georgia Tech

events.name: Notre Dame Fighting Irish at Stanford Cardinal

headlines.description: K.J. Costello threw two of his career-high four touchdown passes in the fourth quarter and No. 20 Stanford rallied for a 38-20 victory over No. 9 Notre Dame on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 20 Stanford beats No. 9 Notre Dame 38-20

video.headline: Stanford sends Notre Dame to their third loss

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Highlight (Stanford sends Notre Dame to their third loss) 2017/11/25 ESHEET SOTFULL

events.name: Ohio State Buckeyes at Michigan Wolverines

headlines.description: Dwayne Haskins replaced injured star J.T. Barrett in the third quarter and led No. 8 Ohio State from behind to beat Michigan 31-20 Saturday for the Buckeyes' sixth straight win in the storied rivalry.
headlines.shortLinkText: Haskins helps No. 8 Ohio State rally to beat Michigan 31-20

events.name: Penn State Nittany Lions at Maryland Terrapins

headlines.description: Trace McSorley threw two touchdown passes and ran for a score to cap an outstanding regular season and carry No. 12 Penn State past Maryland 66-3 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: McSorley leads No. 12 Penn State to 66-3 rout of Maryland

video.headline: Penn State makes easy work of Maryland

events.name: Washington State Cougars at Washington Huskies

headlines.description: Myles Gaskin ran for 192 yards and four touchdowns, Washington forced four turnovers, and the No. 15 Huskies ended No. 14 Washington State's hopes for a Pac-12 North title with a 41-14 thumping Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Purple Haze: Washington routs Washington State 41-14

events.name: Michigan State Spartans at Rutgers Scarlet Knights

headlines.description: Brian Lewerke threw for a touchdown and ran for another and No. 21 Michigan State held the ball for more than 47 minutes in defeating Rutgers 40-7 on Saturday to cap a terrific turnaround season.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 21 Michigan State flips 2016 record, goes 9-3

events.name: Texas A&M Aggies at LSU Tigers

headlines.description: Danny Etling passed 347 yards and three touchdowns and No. 19 LSU beat Texas A&M 45-21 on Saturday night in the regular-season finale for both teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Etling's big night helps No. 19 LSU beat Texas A&M 45-21

video.headline: LSU surges past Texas A&M

events.name: Kansas Jayhawks at Oklahoma State Cowboys

headlines.description: Mason Rudolph passed for 438 yards and two touchdowns and ran for two scores in his final home game to lead No. 18 Oklahoma State to a 58-17 victory over Kansas on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rudolph, No. 18 Oklahoma State rolls over Kansas

video.headline: Rudolph gets second TD on 76-yard pass

events.name: East Carolina Pirates at Memphis Tigers

headlines.description: Riley Ferguson threw for three touchdowns and Darrell Henderson scored twice and rushed for 122 yards as No. 17 Memphis dominated East Carolina 70-13 on Saturday in a tuneup for the American Athletic Conference championship game.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 17 Memphis dominates East Carolina with 70-13 victory

video.headline: Memphis cruises to 49-0 halftime lead in rout

events.name: Northwestern Wildcats at Illinois Fighting Illini

headlines.description: Justin Jackson ran for 144 yards and a touchdown and No. 23 Northwestern won its seventh straight, beating Illinois 42-17 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jackson, defense lead No. 23 Northwestern past Illinois

video.headline: Northwestern runs over Illinois

events.name: Boise State Broncos at Fresno State Bulldogs

headlines.description: Marcus McMaryion threw for 332 yards and two touchdowns and Fresno State beat No. 25 Boise State 28-17 on Saturday in a preview of the Mountain West title game.
headlines.shortLinkText: Fresno State beats No. 25 Boise State 28-17 in title preview

events.name: Florida State Seminoles at Florida Gators

headlines.description: Jacob Pugh and Levonta Taylor turned takeaways into touchdowns and helped Florida State beat in-state rival Florida for the fifth consecutive year, 38-22 Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Florida State uses 2 defensive TDs to beat Florida 38-22

video.headline: Florida State takes down Florida

events.name: Louisville Cardinals at Kentucky Wildcats

headlines.description: Lamar Jackson accounted for 372 yards and two passing touchdowns, along with being involved in a first-quarter fight, Reggie Bonnafon rushed for two scores and Louisville coasted past rival Kentucky 44-17 on Saturday to reclaim the Governor's Cup.
headlines.shortLinkText: Louisville, Lamar Jackson roll past rival Kentucky 44-17

video.headline: Jackson delivers perfect pass for 29-yard TD

events.name: Indiana Hoosiers at Purdue Boilermakers

headlines.description: Jackson Anthrop ran for two scores, Elijah Sindelar threw for two more and Markell Jones rushed for a career high 217 yards Saturday, leading Purdue past Indiana 31-24 and into its first bowl game in five years.

events.name: Tulane Green Wave at SMU Mustangs

headlines.shortLinkText: SMU stops Tulane on goal line as time expires for 41-38 win

events.name: Boston College Eagles at Syracuse Orange

events.name: Duke Blue Devils at Wake Forest Demon Deacons

headlines.shortLinkText: Duke tops Wake Forest 31-23 to become bowl eligible

events.name: North Texas Mean Green at Rice Owls

headlines.shortLinkText: Smith rushes for career-high 178 in North Texas' 30-14 win

Florida Atlantic Owls at Charlotte 49ers

events.name: Arkansas State Red Wolves at Louisiana Monroe Warhawks

events.name: North Carolina Tar Heels at NC State Wolfpack
